name: Lee's Incredible Momos
author: HEYHON53
summary: Momos are traditional Tibetan steamed dumplings. Very easy to make and disappear quickly!
ingredients: 1 (1/2 inch) piece fresh ginger root, grated
directions: Bring 3 inches of water in a large pot of water to a boil
You may also do this with a wok and steamer baskets
In a large bowl, mix together the ground beef, onion, spinach, garlic, 1 teaspoon ginger, green onion, cilantro and salt
Place a spoonful of the filling onto a wonton wrapper; fold and crimp to seal
If necessary, wet the edges with water
Repeat with remaining filling and wrappers
Set a steamer tray in the pot, and place the momos on the steamer
Steam over rapidly boiling water for 30 minutes
To make the dipping sauce, mix together the soy sauce, rice vinegar, chili oil and grated ginger in a small bowl
